# Master Dashboard & Global Search

## Overview
Create a centralized Master Dashboard in LifeOps that serves as a command center for power users. It combines a global search/command palette with cross-module overview widgets, a Cronjobs system, real-time insights, and an approvals queue. The UI must be highly performant, scalable, and permission-aware, with a strong emphasis on a dark, dense, developer-focused aesthetic. The feature should support full-text, fuzzy search across modules, real-time widget updates via WebSockets or polling, and a robust command palette capable of executing actions across modules while preserving an auditable run trail and reversible actions.

Project scope covers:
- A Master Dashboard page (page_master_dashboard_006) that presents global search, quick command bar, an active cronjobs snapshot, cross-module alerts, and quick-access workflows.
- A global search index with permissions-aware results and fuzzy matching.
- A cronjobs management surface with per-run details, next-run previews, retry policies, inputs/outputs, and an approvals queue for actions requiring human review.
- Real-time or near-real-time widgets to reflect system state, agent activity, alerts, and artifacts.

## Components to Build
- Global Search Command Bar
  - Full-text search leveraging a central index (Elasticsearch/Algolia).
  - Fuzzy search with typo tolerance, synonyms, and permission-filtered results.
  - Keyboard shortcuts (e.g., Cmd/Ctrl+K) to open, arrows to navigate, Enter to execute.
  - Result facets and per-result actions (open detail, run quick command, navigate to module).
  - Safeguards: return empty array when no results; guard against null data.
- Master Dashboard Shell
  - Left navigation (collapsible) and top header with mini-controls.
  - Central content area with a responsive card grid and a dense layout.
  - Real-time widgets: Cronjobs snapshot, cross-module alerts, active workflows, and quick-access workflows.
- Cronjobs Dashboard Widget
  - List of cronjobs with: name, status (enabled/paused), schedule, next run, last run outcome, target, inputs/outputs, permissions/automation level, safety rails, retry policy, and logs/diffs.
  - Per-run detail panel: runId, start time, end time, outcome, artifacts, trace, and diffs.
  - Create/Edit cronjob surfaces (UI builder for schedule, timezone, input payload, constraints, safety rails).
  - Approvals queue: a separate panel/list for actions requiring human review, with filter/sort capabilities.
- Cross-Module Alerts Widget
  - Aggregated alert stream from modules (e.g., Dev, Content, Finance, Health) with severity, timestamp, source module, and contextual actions.
  - Ability to acknowledge, mute, or create follow-up tasks.
- Quick-Access Workflows Widget
  - Predefined templates for common tasks (e.g., deploy workflow, run audit, generate report) with one-click execution.
  - Context-aware suggestions based on user role and module permissions.
- Workspace Cards & Layout
  - Re-usable Card components with consistent typography, spacing, and elevation.
  - Card contents: icon, title, subtitle, major metric, small metadata badge, and action controls.
- Data Visualization
  - Lightweight charts for cronjob success rate, run duration distributions, and alert trends.
  - Minimalist axes, muted gridlines, and accent colors from the design system.
- Permission/Access Layer
  - Frontend components that consume a permissioned API surface, ensuring search results and actions are filtered by user permissions.
  - Visual affordances for restricted items (e.g., disabled actions, locked indicators).

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Architecture
  - React-based SPA with a modular component approach.
  - State management with a centralized store (e.g., Zustand/Redux) for dashboard widgets, search state, and user session.
  - Use React Query or SWR for data fetching with caching; ensure null-safe data handling.
- Components & Pages
  - GlobalSearchBar component
    - Props: onSelectResult, onExecuteCommand
    - Behavior: asynchronous search calls; results list with keyboard navigation
    - Safety: guard all array operations with (results ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(results) ? results.map(...) : []
  - MasterDashboardLayout component
    - LeftNav: collapsible sections, active item indicator
    - TopBar: session controls, global search trigger, quick actions
    - ContentGrid: responsive cards grid; supports drag-reorder or fixed layout as per design
  - CronjobsWidget component
    - Table/list view with columns: Name, Schedule, Next Run, Last Run, Status, Target, Actions
    - Per-run detail drawer/panel with structured sections: Inputs, Outputs, Logs, Trace
    - CreateCronjobModal / EditCronjobModal
    - ApprovalsQueue component
  - AlertsWidget component
    - List of alerts with severity color coding; actions to acknowledge, mute, assign
  - QuickWorkflowsWidget component
    - List of templates with a Run button; supports parameter prompts
  - ChartPanel component
    - Reusable for cronjob metrics and alert trends
  - APIErrorBoundary / Toasts
- Data Handling & Safety
  - All API responses must sanitize with defaults:
    - const items = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Guard all array methods:
    - (items ?? []).map(...)
  - useState defaults for arrays/objects:
    - const [widgets, setWidgets] = useState<WidgetType[]>([])
  - Access nested properties via optional chaining: obj?.prop?.subprop
  - Destructuring with defaults:
    - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- API Integration
  - Endpoints for search, cronjobs, alerts, approvals, and quick workflows
  - Real-time updates via WebSockets or long polling for the dashboard widgets
  - Pagination, filtering, and sorting on search results and cronjob lists
- Accessibility
  - Ensure keyboard navigability for the search results and command palette
  - ARIA roles and proper focus management
- Performance & Security
  - Debounce search input; limit payloads; guard against over-fetching
  - Token/permission checks on client; rely on API for final authorization
  - Avoid leaking restricted data in any UI path
- Styling
  - Tailwind-like utility approach or CSS-in-JS that aligns with the project’s design system
  - Apply the provided color palette and typography guidelines
  - Responsive breakpoints to accommodate large monitors and tablets
- Testing
  - Unit tests for utility functions guarding against null/undefined arrays
  - Integration tests for search results respect permissions
  - E2E tests for key flows: global search execution, cronjob creation, approvals workflow

### Backend
- Data Models
  - CronJob
    - id, name, enabled, schedule, timezone, triggerType, target, inputPayload, permissions, automationLevel, constraints, safetyRails, retryPolicy, outputs, logs, lastRun, nextRun, status
  - RunArtifact
    - id, cronJobId, runId, startedAt, endedAt, status, trace, logs, artifacts
  - Approval
    - id, cronJobId, actionType, requestedBy, requestedAt, status, rationale
  - Alert
    - id, sourceModule, severity, message, timestamp, acknowledgedBy, status
  - WorkflowTemplate
    - id, name, description, parameters, requiredPermissions
  - User
  - Permissions
- APIs
  - Search API
    - GET /api/search?q=&filters=&page=&perPage=
    - Supports: full-text search, fuzzy matching, permission filtering
  - Cronjobs API
    - GET /api/cronjobs (list with pagination)
    - POST /api/cronjobs (create)
    - GET /api/cronjobs/{id}
    - PATCH /api/cronjobs/{id} (update)
    - POST /api/cronjobs/{id}/run (manual run)
  - Run Details API
    - GET /api/cronjobs/{id}/runs/{runId}
  - Approvals API
    - GET /api/approvals
    - POST /api/approvals/{id}/approve
    - POST /api/approvals/{id}/reject
  - Alerts API
    - GET /api/alerts
    - POST /api/alerts/{id}/acknowledge
  - Workflows API
    - GET /api/workflows/templates
    - POST /api/workflows/execute
- Security
  - Implement OAuth2/OIDC or session-based authentication
  - Enforce role-based access control (RBAC) on all endpoints
  - Sanitize inputs server-side; validate payload schema with a contract system (e.g., JSON Schema)
  - Audit logs for every create/update/run/approval action
- Validation
  - Validate cron schedule formats; support cron expressions and UI-based schedules
  - Validate inputPayload shapes and required fields
  - Validate permissions and automationLevel constraints
- Real-time
  - WebSocket channel for dashboard widgets; fallback to long-polling
  - Push updates for cronjob runs, alerts, and approvals

### Integration
- Data Flow
  - GlobalSearchBar queries the Search API; results feed into a contextual navigation system that routes to module dashboards or executes quick commands.
  - CronjobsWidget continuously polls or subscribes to cronjob state; per-run details fetch on demand.
  - AlertsWidget subscribes to real-time alert streams; actions route to the Alerts API and update the dashboard state.
  - ApprovalsQueue interacts with Cronjobs and Approvals APIs; status transitions update relevant widgets.
- State Synchronization
  - Use a client-side store to hold:
    - search results, current selection, and active command
    - cronjobs list, nextRun, lastRun status
    - alerts, approvals, workflow templates
  - Ensure all data structures initialize with safe defaults:
    - useState<YourType[]>([]) and guards for nulls
- Error Handling
  - Centralized error boundary with user-friendly messages
  - Retry strategies for transient failures with exponential backoff
- Design System Alignment
  - Reuse Card, Button, Input, Avatar, Icon components from the existing design system
  - Apply the specified color palette and typography
  - Ensure consistency in spacing, borders, and elevation across widgets

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Master Dashboard (page_master_dashboard_006)
   - Top navigation shows a global search trigger; user can press Cmd/Ctrl+K to open the search modal.
2. Global Search
   - User types a query; search results render with permission-filtered items from multiple modules.
   - User navigates results with arrow keys; Enter opens the selected item or executes a quick command.
3. Cronjobs Overview
   - CronjobsWidget presents a snapshot: next run, last run outcome, status, and quick actions (edit, run now, pause).
   - User selects a cronjob to view per-run details; can drill into inputs, outputs, and traces.
4. Approvals Queue
   - Approvals panel lists pending actions requiring review; user can approve or reject with rationale.
   - On approval, the cronjob auto-executes per policy and updates the run history.
5. Alerts & Workflows
   - Real-time alerts appear in AlertsWidget; user can acknowledge or mute.
   - QuickWorkflowsWidget offers one-click execution for common tasks; prompts for required parameters when needed.
6. Real-Time Feedback
   - Widgets refresh in real time or near real time; user interactions trigger optimistic UI updates with server reconciliation.
7. Drill-Down & Audit
   - Actions produce artifacts and run traces for audit trails; user can export diffs and logs.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- CronJob
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - enabled: boolean
  - schedule: string (cron expression or UI-based)
  - timezone: string
  - triggerType: string
  - target: string
  - inputPayload: any
  - permissions: string[]
  - automationLevel: string
  - constraints: { maxActions?: number; spendLimit?: number; allowedTools?: string[] }
  - safetyRails: string[]
  - retryPolicy: { maxRetries: number; backoffMs: number; deadLetter?: string }
  - outputs: RunArtifact[]
  - logs: string[]
  - lastRun?: { runId: string; startedAt: string; endedAt?: string; status: string }
  - nextRun?: string
  - status: string
- RunArtifact
  - id: string
  - cronJobId: string
  - runId: string
  - startedAt: string
  - endedAt: string
  - status: string
  - trace: string
  - logs: string[]
  - artifacts: string[]
- Approval
  - id: string
  - cronJobId: string
  - actionType: string
  - requestedBy: string
  - requestedAt: string
  - status: string
  - rationale: string
- Alert
  - id: string
  - sourceModule: string
  - severity: string
  - message: string
  - timestamp: string
  - acknowledgedBy?: string
  - status: string
- WorkflowTemplate
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - description: string
  - parameters: any
  - requiredPermissions: string[]

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /api/search?q={query}&filters={filters}&page={n}&perPage={m}
- GET /api/cronjobs
- POST /api/cronjobs
- GET /api/cronjobs/{id}
- PATCH /api/cronjobs/{id}
- POST /api/cronjobs/{id}/run
- GET /api/cronjobs/{id}/runs/{runId}
- GET /api/approvals
- POST /api/approvals/{id}/approve
- POST /api/approvals/{id}/reject
- GET /api/alerts
- POST /api/alerts/{id}/acknowledge
- GET /api/workflows/templates
- POST /api/workflows/execute

Security: [Authentication, authorization requirements]
- Implement OAuth2/OIDC or session-based auth; all endpoints enforce RBAC.
- Resource access restricted by user roles and per-item permissions.
- Audit trail for all mutating actions.
- Input validation on server with strict schemas; return 403/401 for unauthorized access.

Validation: [Input validation rules]
- Cron schedules: validate cron expressions; reject invalid schedules with actionable errors.
- Input payloads: schema-validate payloads against defined templates; required fields enforced.
- Approvals: ensure rationale present on reject/approval actions when required.
- Search: sanitize and normalize queries; handle empty queries gracefully.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Global search returns permission-filtered results from all modules with fuzzy matching; results are safely rendered (guarded against nulls) and executable via keyboard commands.
- [ ] Cronjobs surface shows next run times, last run outcomes, and per-run details; approvals queue functions with correct status transitions and audit logs.
- [ ] Real-time/near real-time updates for cronjobs, alerts, and approvals via WebSockets or polling; UI remains responsive with safe default states.
- [ ] All array operations in frontend are guarded: (data ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(data) ? data.map(...) : [].
- [ ] All useState initializations for arrays/objects use proper defaults: useState<Type[]>([]) or useState<Type>({} as Type) where appropriate.
- [ ] API responses are validated to shapes before use: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- [ ] The UI adheres to the provided visual style tokens and typography guidelines; color usage follows the palette strictly.
- [ ] Accessibility: keyboard navigation, proper focus management, and ARIA labels implemented.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Dark, dense, high-contrast UI with controlled color accents.
- Elevation, borders, and subtle gradients as described.
- Card-based layout with intuitive density for power users.
- Consistent typography, spacing, and alignment; 8px baseline grid; 220–260px sidebar.

Visual Style

Color Palette (as provided)
- Primary background: #0B0B0C
- Secondary surface: #151718
- Tertiary surface / panel outline: #1F1F20
- Primary text / headings: #FFFFFF
- Secondary text / meta: #9DA3A6
- Subtle text / disabled: #56595B
- Accent (action / alert): #FF3B30
- Neutral highlight / icon fill: #CFCFCF
- Soft highlight / gloss: #E6E7E8
- Chart/status accents: teal #00C2A8, amber #FFB020, purple #8B5CF6
- Borders / dividers: rgba(255,255,255,0.03)
- Gradients: #111213 → #1A1A1B

Typography & Layout
- Font: Inter / SF Pro Display / Roboto fallback
- Headings: 20–28px, weight 600–700
- Card titles: 14–16px, weight 500–600
- Body: 12–14px, weight 400
- Microcopy: 11–12px, weight 300–400
- Spacing: 8px baseline grid; gutters 220–260px; header 56–64px; card padding 16–20px
- Alignment: left-aligned lists; mixed layout for main content; dense vertical spacing in trees/lists

Key Design Elements
- Card: dark, elevated, rounded 8–12px; gradient background; inner top highlight
- Navigation: left vertical with active accent pill; collapsible sections
- Data Visualization: minimal charts with subdued grids and colored series
- Interactive Elements: primary/secondary buttons, inputs, toggles, chips, micro-interactions
- Badges: counts and alerts with appropriate color usage

Connected Pages
- Master Dashboard: Global search, quick command bar, cronjobs snapshot, cross-module alerts, quick-access workflows.

